1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:12,000
(Watch on www.dramacool.club Support Admin)

2
00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:01,200
[Disclaimer:
All depicted events are fictional

3
00:00:01,240 --> 00:00:02,400
and for entertainment purposes only;
viewer discretion is advised]

4
00:00:13,760 --> 00:00:18,560
[Love Upon a Time Series]

5
00:00:18,630 --> 00:00:19,920
After all,

6
00:00:20,220 --> 00:00:24,400
we shall soon be family.

7
00:00:26,320 --> 00:00:27,840
He's about to get married.

8
00:00:28,050 --> 00:00:30,840
Complete the mission and return home.

9
00:00:31,570 --> 00:00:33,800
You'd be better off
quitting the game before it starts, Nakun!

10
00:00:47,840 --> 00:00:49,210
My Lord,

11
00:00:49,320 --> 00:00:51,100
what flower might this be?

12
00:00:54,400 --> 00:00:55,920
My Lord...

13
00:01:00,320 --> 00:01:01,320
Master Klao.

14
00:01:01,930 --> 00:01:02,810
Come now, Master.

15
00:01:02,840 --> 00:01:04,819
You behave like a mere child,
inviting me to play at hide-and-seek.

16
00:01:07,180 --> 00:01:10,230
What are you... gazing at so intently?

17
00:01:12,770 --> 00:01:13,600
Come on!

18
00:01:23,010 --> 00:01:24,520
Oh? Is that...

19
00:01:28,980 --> 00:01:30,920
Meow.

20
00:01:33,960 --> 00:01:35,120
A grumpy cat.

21
00:01:36,900 --> 00:01:38,009
A cat?

22
00:01:38,390 --> 00:01:41,520
Does your manor also house a cat, my Lord?

23
00:01:43,120 --> 00:01:46,020
Indeed, a Khao Manee cat,

24
00:01:46,560 --> 00:01:48,240
pure white from head to tail.

25
00:01:49,240 --> 00:01:51,090
It is at times quite affectionate,

26
00:01:51,830 --> 00:01:53,430
yet at others remarkably playful.

27
00:01:58,130 --> 00:02:01,040
Why am I so emotional and jealous of her?

28
00:02:01,070 --> 00:02:05,740
He doesn't like me. He likes Klao.
I can't afford to fall for him.

29
00:02:08,370 --> 00:02:11,830
Although back at the temple,
Klao's story really resonated with me.

30
00:02:12,290 --> 00:02:14,690
When the fortune teller
talked about Klao's spirit, I even cried.

31
00:02:14,840 --> 00:02:18,110
So what's going on?

32
00:02:18,230 --> 00:02:19,760
Let us be on our way, Lady Varna.

33
00:02:20,130 --> 00:02:22,590
I fear High Lord Soontrapinit
has been awaiting us in vain.

34
00:02:23,900 --> 00:02:25,090
Yes, my Lord.

35
00:02:43,840 --> 00:02:45,240
Master.

36
00:02:45,730 --> 00:02:46,730
What?

37
00:02:47,380 --> 00:02:48,800
May we set forth now?

38
00:02:49,370 --> 00:02:50,410
Why?

39
00:02:52,680 --> 00:02:53,680
Whoa!

40
00:02:59,230 --> 00:03:00,650
What seems to be the matter here?

41
00:03:01,980 --> 00:03:02,980
Uh...

42
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:05,520
Exercise.

43
00:03:06,550 --> 00:03:07,550
Lesson one.

44
00:03:08,510 --> 00:03:11,840
Up, down, up, down, up, and down.

45
00:03:11,870 --> 00:03:13,160
Allow me to demonstrate.

46
00:03:28,680 --> 00:03:31,180
[Love Upon a Time Series]

47
00:04:40,720 --> 00:04:44,720
[Love Upon a Time Series]

48
00:04:57,240 --> 00:04:58,350
Lady Varna

49
00:04:58,810 --> 00:05:00,900
possesses exquisite grace
and refined conduct,

50
00:05:01,010 --> 00:05:02,330
which together form
the very essence of a lady.

51
00:05:02,940 --> 00:05:04,920
Truly, she is most suited
to stand by Phop's side.

52
00:05:05,490 --> 00:05:07,290
- Father.
- Hm?

53
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:13,880
What about you, Dear Klao?

54
00:05:14,600 --> 00:05:16,840
Have you set your sights
upon any particular lady?

55
00:05:18,410 --> 00:05:21,230
Well, I...

56
00:05:21,490 --> 00:05:23,160
I...

57
00:05:23,900 --> 00:05:25,560
Answer when an elder inquires.

58
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,680
Do not make her wait.

59
00:05:30,440 --> 00:05:32,720
I have yet to set my sights upon any.

60
00:05:34,330 --> 00:05:36,800
Then you must hasten to do so.

61
00:05:37,330 --> 00:05:40,640
You, too, should see to it that
you are properly wed without further delay

62
00:05:40,670 --> 00:05:42,380
before committing yourself
to royal service;

63
00:05:42,500 --> 00:05:44,520
only then shall you be
a man of true credibility.

64
00:05:45,020 --> 00:05:48,080
Royal... service?

65
00:05:48,600 --> 00:05:49,600
What?

66
00:05:51,020 --> 00:05:54,720
You spoke to me of your desire
to enter royal service, even as your father did.

67
00:05:55,170 --> 00:05:56,870
Now that you are fully recovered,

68
00:05:57,210 --> 00:05:59,640
return to your studies
with renewed diligence.

69
00:05:59,820 --> 00:06:02,520
I shall arrange for a master
to guide your studies.

70
00:06:08,410 --> 00:06:10,400
I can guide him, Father.

71
00:06:12,080 --> 00:06:15,120
You crazy guy!
Why did you tell him that?

72
00:06:17,630 --> 00:06:18,630
Very well.

73
00:06:19,750 --> 00:06:22,520
He has already come of age at twenty.

74
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:25,840
He can no longer afford to
idle his time away so aimlessly.

75
00:06:27,710 --> 00:06:33,040
I entrust you to guide Dear Klao
in all that he ought to know.

76
00:06:34,550 --> 00:06:35,560
Understood, Father.

77
00:07:02,700 --> 00:07:04,780
Committing to royal service,
like Klao's father did?

78
00:07:22,020 --> 00:07:25,400
Why didn't Phop object to his father
about Klao's marriage,

79
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:29,950
even though he seems into Klao?

80
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:47,020
Maybe...

81
00:07:48,680 --> 00:07:50,040
Bromance?

82
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:52,960
Or...

83
00:07:56,240 --> 00:07:57,670
He hasn't realized it yet?

84
00:08:01,220 --> 00:08:02,360
Or...

85
00:08:04,020 --> 00:08:05,900
He's bisexual?

86
00:08:08,500 --> 00:08:09,640
Or...

87
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:15,360
He hasn't come out yet?

88
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,520
If you intend to study,
why have you not sought the study hall?

89
00:08:24,670 --> 00:08:26,420
I have brought you
these volumes of knowledge.

90
00:08:29,830 --> 00:08:31,110
What were you writing just now?

91
00:08:32,970 --> 00:08:34,280
Hey, hey!

92
00:08:35,049 --> 00:08:36,799
Can you not? This one is private!

93
00:08:37,120 --> 00:08:39,000
Have I become a stranger to you?

94
00:08:39,789 --> 00:08:41,640
Am I not being clear? I said no!

95
00:09:26,310 --> 00:09:28,760
Why do you turn away from me?

96
00:09:31,790 --> 00:09:33,560
Is your heart troubled on account of Varna?

97
00:09:36,420 --> 00:09:37,490
No, it isn't.

98
00:09:38,160 --> 00:09:40,160
If so, what then brought you to the garden,

99
00:09:42,130 --> 00:09:43,640
Grumpy Cat?

100
00:09:49,280 --> 00:09:51,320
I was out for a walk,

101
00:09:51,910 --> 00:09:53,640
stretching as I went.

102
00:09:54,680 --> 00:09:55,680
Why?

103
00:09:56,720 --> 00:09:57,720
Are there rules

104
00:09:57,750 --> 00:09:58,850
in this manor that say

105
00:09:59,220 --> 00:10:01,040
I'm not allowed to take a walk
in the garden?

106
00:10:03,050 --> 00:10:04,000
Let it be so.

107
00:10:04,880 --> 00:10:06,360
I shall take your word for it.

108
00:10:08,050 --> 00:10:09,260
Let us now commence your studies.

109
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:26,000
I can't read any of this.

110
00:10:49,660 --> 00:10:50,680
I think...

111
00:10:52,580 --> 00:10:55,720
Phop, can we learn something else first?

112
00:11:14,270 --> 00:11:16,000
Is this what you wish to learn?

113
00:11:16,640 --> 00:11:17,440
How odd.

114
00:11:18,400 --> 00:11:20,520
You once rowed with the speed
of a flying spear.

115
00:11:21,640 --> 00:11:23,190
You keep saying
I once did this and that.

116
00:11:23,230 --> 00:11:25,400
Things aren't the same anymore, are they?

117
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:28,560
This isn't the same person, you know?

118
00:11:54,440 --> 00:11:56,800
Deep and steady.

119
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,890
Then lift it upward.

120
00:12:05,690 --> 00:12:07,120
Do not merely skim the surface.

121
00:12:12,210 --> 00:12:14,040
Remember to alternate your strokes.

122
00:12:33,310 --> 00:12:35,560
That's enough. I can row it myself.

123
00:12:37,490 --> 00:12:38,800
Yet you told me to guide you.

124
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:42,460
You did,
so you should let me try it myself.

125
00:12:42,500 --> 00:12:44,200
This will show how good a mentor you are.

126
00:12:47,370 --> 00:12:50,280
- Hey! Let go!
- Klao, be still,

127
00:12:50,310 --> 00:12:53,200
- lest you capsize the boat.
- Then hands off!

128
00:12:54,590 --> 00:12:55,480
Hey.

129
00:12:58,250 --> 00:12:59,130
Hey!

130
00:12:59,520 --> 00:13:01,640
Let go! Let it go!!

131
00:13:02,320 --> 00:13:03,660
Hands off. Come on.

132
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:04,920
Be still, Klao!

133
00:13:19,800 --> 00:13:20,800
Phop?

134
00:13:22,750 --> 00:13:23,750
Phop...

135
00:13:26,470 --> 00:13:27,470
Phop?

136
00:13:29,680 --> 00:13:30,680
Phop!

137
00:13:31,710 --> 00:13:33,850
Phop, don't do this.

138
00:13:34,720 --> 00:13:36,050
This isn't funny.

139
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:43,990
Phop...

140
00:13:44,520 --> 00:13:45,520
Phop.

141
00:13:45,880 --> 00:13:47,280
Phop! Phop!

142
00:13:48,110 --> 00:13:49,110
Phop!

143
00:13:50,050 --> 00:13:51,050
Phop!!

144
00:14:07,130 --> 00:14:11,230
Phop... Come on,
tell me you're gonna be fine.

145
00:14:16,280 --> 00:14:19,080
Where are you? Phop!

146
00:14:26,670 --> 00:14:27,670
Phop?

147
00:14:28,440 --> 00:14:29,900
Where are you?

148
00:14:30,310 --> 00:14:31,310
Phop!

149
00:14:32,920 --> 00:14:33,800
Phop!!

150
00:14:33,840 --> 00:14:35,000
I am right here.

151
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,320
Phop!

152
00:14:50,460 --> 00:14:51,460
Phop!!

153
00:14:59,740 --> 00:15:01,240
I am more than pleased.

154
00:15:05,710 --> 00:15:06,950
Why are you pleased?

155
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:08,730
You...

156
00:15:09,100 --> 00:15:10,600
Were you pulling my leg?

157
00:15:12,080 --> 00:15:14,040
I was worried sick about you!

158
00:15:15,910 --> 00:15:17,360
That is why I am pleased.

159
00:15:19,040 --> 00:15:21,040
My concern for you is not unrequited.

160
00:15:42,720 --> 00:15:47,120
[What is this feeling?]

161
00:15:49,220 --> 00:15:54,960
If I can't beat this feeling,
why not just embrace it?

162
00:16:14,770 --> 00:16:15,480
Swoosh!

163
00:16:15,560 --> 00:16:16,390
Whoa.

164
00:16:17,810 --> 00:16:18,810
Whoa...

165
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:21,670
Did people in the past spar

166
00:16:21,700 --> 00:16:24,030
the way we go to the gym
or work out in the park?

167
00:16:24,540 --> 00:16:25,740
- Argh!
- Whoa!

168
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:29,600
Ha!

169
00:16:30,440 --> 00:16:31,360
Ow!

170
00:16:36,090 --> 00:16:37,090
Klao,

171
00:16:38,610 --> 00:16:39,800
do kindly come
and enjoy this with me.

172
00:16:41,130 --> 00:16:42,340
Kaew? You're here, too?

173
00:16:42,790 --> 00:16:45,440
You like watching sword fighting?

174
00:16:46,130 --> 00:16:47,130
Not quite.

175
00:16:47,230 --> 00:16:49,840
I am merely here out of concern for Jom.

176
00:16:51,760 --> 00:16:53,040
- Ha!
- Ha!

177
00:16:53,070 --> 00:16:54,440
Whoa!

178
00:16:55,320 --> 00:16:56,120
Whoa...

179
00:17:20,750 --> 00:17:22,400
Alas.

180
00:17:22,790 --> 00:17:23,720
Blood...

181
00:17:39,540 --> 00:17:41,360
Step back. Leave me be.

182
00:17:48,370 --> 00:17:49,870
He never ceases to reprimand me.

183
00:17:55,500 --> 00:17:56,830
Well, Thee is...

184
00:17:57,440 --> 00:18:00,200
I mean, the Physician
is worried about you, Pun.

185
00:18:01,010 --> 00:18:02,680
I mean, Kaew.

186
00:18:03,500 --> 00:18:06,220
You might get hurt while they're sparring.

187
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:09,240
How would you know, Klao?

188
00:18:09,890 --> 00:18:11,730
Such is his way.

189
00:18:12,790 --> 00:18:16,520
Whenever I try to draw close to Jom,
he invariably pushes me away.

190
00:18:19,480 --> 00:18:20,480
You guys are the same.

191
00:18:20,790 --> 00:18:21,720
Hm?

192
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:23,940
Oh...

193
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,470
I have friends in Phichit.

194
00:18:27,190 --> 00:18:29,220
They are similar to you...

195
00:18:29,260 --> 00:18:31,400
and the Physician.

196
00:18:33,390 --> 00:18:35,520
The closer one gets,

197
00:18:36,330 --> 00:18:38,180
the further the other pulls away.

198
00:18:39,690 --> 00:18:41,000
Mm...

199
00:18:41,500 --> 00:18:42,800
A bilabial stop

200
00:18:43,190 --> 00:18:45,520
is a sound produced by blocking
airflow with both lips,

201
00:18:45,900 --> 00:18:47,840
such as /b/ and /p/.

202
00:18:48,680 --> 00:18:50,200
That's correct.

203
00:18:50,750 --> 00:18:51,750
And...

204
00:18:51,920 --> 00:18:52,960
what about this sound?

205
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,120
Is it considered one?

206
00:18:59,050 --> 00:19:00,360
Let's continue, Nakun.

207
00:19:00,880 --> 00:19:04,200
What are the alveolar consonants?

208
00:19:04,740 --> 00:19:06,800
Sounds produced with the tongue
close to the alveolar ridge.

209
00:19:07,850 --> 00:19:08,560
Such as

210
00:19:09,220 --> 00:19:13,040
S, Z, L,

211
00:19:13,380 --> 00:19:16,270
N, D, and

212
00:19:16,310 --> 00:19:17,760
- T.
- Yes, Pun?

213
00:19:18,160 --> 00:19:20,900
So you've given me a nickname now?

214
00:19:20,970 --> 00:19:22,560
You're starting to fall for me, aren't you?

215
00:19:23,200 --> 00:19:24,200
He didn't call you.

216
00:19:24,720 --> 00:19:25,640
He was talking to me.

217
00:19:29,050 --> 00:19:31,430
If I write it like this in IPA,

218
00:19:31,650 --> 00:19:32,600
can you read it?

219
00:19:33,880 --> 00:19:34,560
Here it is.

220
00:19:36,290 --> 00:19:38,720
[I like you, you know?]

221
00:19:43,540 --> 00:19:44,200
Thee.

222
00:19:44,300 --> 00:19:45,400
My lips are parched.

223
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,760
Yes, Pun.

224
00:19:48,040 --> 00:19:49,040
A cup of pure matcha,

225
00:19:49,240 --> 00:19:50,160
no sugar!

226
00:19:51,320 --> 00:19:52,400
Thee

227
00:19:52,490 --> 00:19:54,500
is always so clingy to Pun that

228
00:19:54,710 --> 00:19:56,520
he's like a puppy following a pretty face.

229
00:19:57,220 --> 00:19:58,560
His mindset is this:

230
00:19:58,910 --> 00:20:01,560
"Constant dripping wears away the stone."

231
00:20:02,900 --> 00:20:04,960
However, it's not wearing away at all.

232
00:20:05,950 --> 00:20:06,840
It won't budge.

233
00:20:08,000 --> 00:20:12,000
I never imagined that we should sit together,
sharing laughter once more,

234
00:20:12,510 --> 00:20:15,840
even though I have not
the slightest inkling of what you said.

235
00:20:19,940 --> 00:20:20,840
But...

236
00:20:21,140 --> 00:20:22,480
I just want to say

237
00:20:23,400 --> 00:20:25,130
it's not like he despises you or anything.

238
00:20:28,610 --> 00:20:30,910
If he were,
he wouldn't let you follow him around.

239
00:20:32,890 --> 00:20:33,720
Maybe

240
00:20:33,960 --> 00:20:35,240
he's just shy,

241
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:37,320
or maybe

242
00:20:38,040 --> 00:20:40,640
in this day and age it's not acceptable...

243
00:20:41,270 --> 00:20:44,240
That's why he can't accept your love.

244
00:20:45,980 --> 00:20:47,280
Come now!

245
00:20:47,630 --> 00:20:48,960
I am a man.

246
00:20:49,280 --> 00:20:51,200
How can I give my heart
to one such as myself?

247
00:20:53,770 --> 00:20:54,770
That's fine.

248
00:20:55,280 --> 00:20:56,240
I can tell.

249
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,960
I listen; I don't judge.

250
00:21:09,700 --> 00:21:12,200
Uh, Kaew...

251
00:21:14,500 --> 00:21:17,820
Phop isn't taken?

252
00:21:18,490 --> 00:21:19,190
I mean...

253
00:21:20,140 --> 00:21:21,200
He has not yet taken a spouse?

254
00:21:25,860 --> 00:21:28,080
Or do you think

255
00:21:29,280 --> 00:21:30,520
he likes men,

256
00:21:31,800 --> 00:21:33,000
like you do?

257
00:21:33,840 --> 00:21:35,600
Klao!

258
00:21:36,380 --> 00:21:39,800
You must not speak of him so before others.

259
00:21:43,840 --> 00:21:45,520
So...

260
00:21:46,450 --> 00:21:48,040
he's into men?

261
00:21:55,520 --> 00:21:56,960
That I do not know.

262
00:21:58,100 --> 00:21:59,840
As the rumors go,

263
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,330
Lord Phop

264
00:22:01,470 --> 00:22:02,720
resembles a war elephant

265
00:22:02,970 --> 00:22:05,200
whose strength
is already spent before the first strike.

266
00:22:06,590 --> 00:22:07,300
Uh...

267
00:22:08,300 --> 00:22:09,000
A flame without a spark.

268
00:22:10,000 --> 00:22:10,680
A flag that will not fly.

269
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:12,480
A sword gone dull.

270
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:14,240
Noodles without broth.

271
00:22:14,270 --> 00:22:15,370
A songbird gone silent.

272
00:22:15,410 --> 00:22:16,360
A man bereft of his vigor.

273
00:22:16,600 --> 00:22:17,960
That's enough.

274
00:22:20,890 --> 00:22:21,890
Phop...

275
00:22:22,540 --> 00:22:24,760
Despite looking that strong,

276
00:22:25,280 --> 00:22:28,280
his little guy doesn't work?

277
00:22:30,720 --> 00:22:31,800
His brother, do you mean?

278
00:22:32,900 --> 00:22:34,960
He is yet too small.

279
00:22:35,040 --> 00:22:36,280
He cannot undertake any real work.

280
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:40,000
His is too small?

281
00:22:44,620 --> 00:22:45,680
Too small.

282
00:22:47,600 --> 00:22:49,420
His is small.

283
00:22:50,370 --> 00:22:51,080
Klao!

284
00:22:52,740 --> 00:22:53,590
Ahem!

285
00:22:57,570 --> 00:22:58,570
Klao,

286
00:23:00,460 --> 00:23:02,100
I should like to see
the swordplay of Phichit.

287
00:23:04,120 --> 00:23:05,800
Pray, let me see your art.

288
00:23:28,370 --> 00:23:29,720
- Ow!
- Master Klao.

289
00:23:29,750 --> 00:23:31,170
- Klao.
- Klao?

290
00:23:31,750 --> 00:23:33,530
- Klao?!
- Argh!

291
00:23:34,530 --> 00:23:36,230
- Klao!
- Klao.

292
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:37,360
Master Klao.

293
00:23:38,160 --> 00:23:39,080
Master Klao!

294
00:23:39,530 --> 00:23:41,680
Fetch him the herbal remedy at once.

295
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:46,600
The Buddha, the Dhamma, the Sangha...

296
00:23:46,630 --> 00:23:48,000
What ails Master now?

297
00:23:48,090 --> 00:23:49,560
Physician, I beseech you,
lend us your cure.

298
00:23:54,290 --> 00:23:55,820
His internal elements seem stable.

299
00:23:55,850 --> 00:23:58,680
He must be brought to my manor
for closer examination.

300
00:24:04,500 --> 00:24:05,500
Master Klao.

301
00:24:10,400 --> 00:24:12,430
I'm fine.

302
00:24:13,340 --> 00:24:14,410
I just felt a bit uncomfortable.

303
00:24:15,900 --> 00:24:17,210
I need to get some rest.

304
00:24:18,720 --> 00:24:20,040
Wait for me, Master.

305
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:37,120
Physician, I pray you,
follow him and see to his well-being.

306
00:24:38,620 --> 00:24:41,180
It was but a fleeting ache.
Seeing how he now strides so effortlessly,

307
00:24:41,530 --> 00:24:42,600
there is no cause for concern.

308
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:46,120
I suspect he was simply too slothful
for swordplay and thus feigned illness.

309
00:24:46,680 --> 00:24:47,730
However, I believe...

310
00:24:47,920 --> 00:24:50,280
it would be best to conduct
a thorough examination once more.

311
00:24:50,540 --> 00:24:51,720
Why such concern?

312
00:24:51,850 --> 00:24:53,250
His condition is far from grave.

313
00:24:54,460 --> 00:24:57,180
When you were whispering and laughing with him,
he appeared perfectly content,

314
00:24:57,570 --> 00:24:58,960
without a trace of illness.

315
00:24:59,330 --> 00:25:00,920
Since when have I shared such jests?

316
00:25:00,980 --> 00:25:02,800
Throughout the entirety of the sparring.

317
00:25:03,450 --> 00:25:04,940
You ought to take up the blade yourself,

318
00:25:05,000 --> 00:25:07,280
that you may safeguard
your wife and children.

319
00:25:08,660 --> 00:25:11,580
Stay out of my affairs. I have never harbored
any desire for a wife or children.

320
00:25:18,200 --> 00:25:19,440
What is wrong with him?

321
00:25:23,080 --> 00:25:25,720
Do you truly not know,
or are you merely feigning ignorance?

322
00:25:26,850 --> 00:25:29,200
The feelings between you and Dear Kaew

323
00:25:30,150 --> 00:25:31,360
are plain as day.

324
00:25:33,640 --> 00:25:34,810
Do not seek to conceal them.

325
00:25:36,350 --> 00:25:39,320
I harbor no feelings for him whatsoever,
only annoyance.

326
00:25:40,570 --> 00:25:41,570
My good Physician,

327
00:25:43,000 --> 00:25:45,370
we cannot know for how long
those who stand beside us

328
00:25:45,670 --> 00:25:47,240
shall remain.

329
00:25:48,270 --> 00:25:51,160
The morrow might bring a parting
we never foresaw.

330
00:25:53,940 --> 00:25:57,060
Once before, I nearly lost
all that I held dear.

331
00:25:58,780 --> 00:26:00,980
I know too well the agony it brings.

332
00:26:02,910 --> 00:26:04,760
I wish for such sorrow
never to strike again,

333
00:26:07,110 --> 00:26:08,700
neither upon myself

334
00:26:10,350 --> 00:26:11,720
nor upon my friend.

335
00:26:59,310 --> 00:27:00,880
Don't get sidetracked.

336
00:27:01,600 --> 00:27:03,070
Continue the mission.

337
00:27:05,710 --> 00:27:07,520
Klao was killed.

338
00:27:09,130 --> 00:27:11,180
This might be the real mission:

339
00:27:11,830 --> 00:27:13,360
who killed Klao?

340
00:27:26,990 --> 00:27:29,010
Mother, Lady Varna,

341
00:27:29,080 --> 00:27:31,110
where did you find such blossoms?

342
00:27:31,230 --> 00:27:32,520
Their fragrance fills the air.

343
00:27:33,220 --> 00:27:34,450
I have only just learned of

344
00:27:34,680 --> 00:27:38,370
Lady Varna's renowned skill
in the art of traditional potpourri.

345
00:27:38,710 --> 00:27:42,000
So exceptional was her craft that
she once served the High Lord of Lopburi himself.

346
00:27:43,960 --> 00:27:47,080
It is said that the craft of perfumery
demands the utmost meticulousness.

347
00:27:47,870 --> 00:27:49,960
As such, your skill
must truly be of the finest order.

348
00:27:51,490 --> 00:27:53,720
You are most kind with your words, my Lord.

349
00:27:55,940 --> 00:27:57,790
I was utterly charmed by the fragrance,

350
00:27:57,820 --> 00:27:59,640
so I entreated her to come
and craft more for us.

351
00:27:59,800 --> 00:28:02,850
We shall soon craft a fragrance
for your pleasure, Phop.

352
00:28:03,200 --> 00:28:05,420
Kindly join me and choose the scent.

353
00:28:05,510 --> 00:28:06,770
I leave the choice to you, Mother.

354
00:28:07,420 --> 00:28:09,180
Having just practiced with the blade,

355
00:28:09,410 --> 00:28:11,500
I must wash

356
00:28:11,660 --> 00:28:13,560
before attending to my duties
with the patrol.

357
00:28:19,660 --> 00:28:23,360
It seems he cares little for me, does he?

358
00:28:25,960 --> 00:28:28,110
Do not speak thus, Lady Varna.

359
00:28:28,620 --> 00:28:30,000
Who could fail to admire one

360
00:28:30,070 --> 00:28:32,680
so fair and accomplished as you?

361
00:28:33,600 --> 00:28:34,840
I believe

362
00:28:35,190 --> 00:28:38,680
he is merely indifferent
to such trifling matters.

363
00:28:40,560 --> 00:28:41,560
Yes, my Lady.

364
00:28:57,700 --> 00:29:00,390
For all his stern demeanor,

365
00:29:00,920 --> 00:29:02,190
the truth is that

366
00:29:02,640 --> 00:29:04,520
Phop is merely a bashful soul.

367
00:29:06,030 --> 00:29:08,970
Pray, do make an effort to visit
our manor more often, Lady Varna,

368
00:29:09,310 --> 00:29:10,670
and we shall become better acquainted.

369
00:29:12,180 --> 00:29:13,180
But...

370
00:29:13,500 --> 00:29:15,790
would such a thing be seemly, my Lady?

371
00:29:17,130 --> 00:29:18,210
Of course.

372
00:29:19,280 --> 00:29:21,430
Should anyone inquire,

373
00:29:21,470 --> 00:29:24,390
say I have asked for your presence
to instruct me in perfumery.

374
00:29:25,290 --> 00:29:27,540
And should there be any malicious gossip,

375
00:29:27,820 --> 00:29:30,720
inform me at once.
I shall deal with it accordingly.

376
00:29:30,940 --> 00:29:33,980
Then I am most willing, my Lady.

377
00:29:45,450 --> 00:29:46,360
Aunt...

378
00:29:47,280 --> 00:29:48,280
Lady Varna...

379
00:29:49,490 --> 00:29:51,630
Can you teach me how to make potpourri?

380
00:30:09,140 --> 00:30:11,000
This is rather a surprise.

381
00:30:12,050 --> 00:30:13,630
I never once imagined

382
00:30:14,020 --> 00:30:17,280
you would take an interest in
such domestic crafts, Dear Klao.

383
00:30:17,850 --> 00:30:19,920
I thought you preferred
your scrolls and volumes.

384
00:30:20,730 --> 00:30:21,600
Well...

385
00:30:21,990 --> 00:30:24,990
I want to make myself useful,
given a chance.

386
00:30:25,530 --> 00:30:28,880
Perhaps I might further
endear myself to you.

387
00:30:29,030 --> 00:30:30,030
My!

388
00:30:31,420 --> 00:30:35,240
My heart is already
so full of fondness for you, Dear Klao.

389
00:30:35,320 --> 00:30:37,120
Oh, you...

390
00:30:42,990 --> 00:30:44,980
Does your stomach no longer trouble you?

391
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:47,040
Oh...

392
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:51,320
It has subsided, Phop.

393
00:30:51,480 --> 00:30:53,980
That's why I'm out here with Aunt.

394
00:30:58,520 --> 00:31:00,260
What a relief.

395
00:31:01,190 --> 00:31:02,890
Then I must take my leave for patrol.

396
00:31:06,490 --> 00:31:07,360
Understood.

397
00:31:10,100 --> 00:31:11,890
I must bid you farewell for now, Mother

398
00:31:13,410 --> 00:31:14,410
and Lady Varna.

399
00:31:27,540 --> 00:31:29,080
What's next,

400
00:31:29,720 --> 00:31:30,780
Lady Varna?

401
00:31:32,320 --> 00:31:33,320
Uh...

402
00:31:33,840 --> 00:31:35,760
It is done this way, Klao.

403
00:31:56,610 --> 00:31:58,810
Yes! He's finally gone.

404
00:32:06,000 --> 00:32:07,080
Uh...

405
00:32:07,520 --> 00:32:11,360
The flowers Phop favors
are nowhere to be found here.

406
00:32:14,130 --> 00:32:16,310
But Aunt said

407
00:32:16,420 --> 00:32:19,560
he does not favor such trifling matters.

408
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:23,200
How come?

409
00:32:23,530 --> 00:32:25,370
Phop

410
00:32:25,570 --> 00:32:28,920
just asked me to fetch him flowers
by the manor

411
00:32:29,710 --> 00:32:31,370
and bring them to his room.

412
00:32:32,410 --> 00:32:35,620
Their fragrance filled the air.

413
00:32:44,740 --> 00:32:46,990
With that said,

414
00:32:47,260 --> 00:32:51,280
let me pick some more flowers for him.

415
00:33:02,850 --> 00:33:06,730
Yes, I've finally made it out!
My plan is working:

416
00:33:06,780 --> 00:33:11,780
wait for Phop to go on patrol, sneak to
the market, and return before he catches me!

417
00:33:11,870 --> 00:33:14,040
Let's complete the mission and return home!

418
00:33:14,110 --> 00:33:16,440
I refuse to be stuck here
just to get married.

419
00:33:28,010 --> 00:33:29,010
Kong!

420
00:33:29,850 --> 00:33:31,040
What are you doing here?

421
00:33:35,120 --> 00:33:37,900
And what of you, Master?
What brings you to this place?

422
00:33:38,360 --> 00:33:40,720
Might you be going to that place?

423
00:33:41,450 --> 00:33:42,450
"That place"?

424
00:33:43,610 --> 00:33:44,460
What do you mean?

425
00:33:44,490 --> 00:33:47,190
Good heavens, there is no need to keep
such secrets from me, Master.

426
00:33:47,750 --> 00:33:49,760
We both know
you visit that place most often,

427
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:53,400
the House of Pleasure

428
00:33:53,690 --> 00:33:55,340
at the farthest end of the market.

429
00:33:56,260 --> 00:33:59,190
"The House of Pleasure"? A brothel?!

430
00:33:59,220 --> 00:34:02,360
Klao often went to the market
for this place?!

431
00:34:02,890 --> 00:34:03,890
Master Klao,

432
00:34:04,130 --> 00:34:05,280
allow me to accompany you.

433
00:34:09,010 --> 00:34:10,440
I beg of you, Master.

434
00:34:18,610 --> 00:34:19,360
Sure thing.

435
00:34:20,020 --> 00:34:20,840
Let's go.

436
00:34:21,639 --> 00:34:22,380
Yes!

437
00:34:33,840 --> 00:34:34,750
Let's go, shall we?

438
00:34:34,880 --> 00:34:36,000
Yes, Master Klao...

439
00:34:42,929 --> 00:34:43,730
Alright!

440
00:34:45,960 --> 00:34:48,190
Master Klao, I am unable to swim.

441
00:34:48,840 --> 00:34:49,840
It's fine.

442
00:34:50,179 --> 00:34:51,850
Swim after my boat, okay?

443
00:34:52,900 --> 00:34:54,320
Uh... Master...

444
00:35:05,840 --> 00:35:07,360
Be wary.

445
00:35:07,420 --> 00:35:09,400
Thank you.

446
00:35:17,170 --> 00:35:22,190
A multicultural market! Feels like the ones in
Khaosan Road, Pattaya, and Patpong.

447
00:35:22,430 --> 00:35:24,840
No wonder Klao loved coming to this place.

448
00:35:24,940 --> 00:35:25,850
Oh!

449
00:35:25,920 --> 00:35:27,140
I'm sorry, sir.

450
00:35:27,540 --> 00:35:29,160
Uh, excuse me.

451
00:35:30,110 --> 00:35:31,110
This place...

452
00:35:31,750 --> 00:35:32,930
What is this market called?

453
00:35:34,030 --> 00:35:35,280
It is known as a canal market.

454
00:35:38,160 --> 00:35:40,360
You must have only just arrived
from the countryside.

455
00:35:49,450 --> 00:35:52,200
Okay, I'm at the right place,

456
00:35:52,640 --> 00:35:53,920
but where's the brothel?

457
00:35:55,630 --> 00:35:57,240
I hope Kong was just spitting nonsense.

458
00:35:57,500 --> 00:36:02,070
Klao was heartbroken over his father's affair.
He probably didn't enjoy the brothel, did he?

459
00:36:11,110 --> 00:36:13,760
The sweets remain untouched.
He has certainly not set foot in the kitchen.

460
00:36:14,860 --> 00:36:16,200
- Is he not in his bed?!
- Is he not in the garden?!

461
00:36:17,220 --> 00:36:19,770
I searched far and wide,
but he was nowhere to be found.

462
00:36:19,800 --> 00:36:20,810
Argh!

463
00:36:20,850 --> 00:36:21,920
How utterly dim-witted!

464
00:36:22,060 --> 00:36:23,680
A wrong husband,
and a lifetime's regret.

465
00:36:23,850 --> 00:36:24,720
Regret, I say!

466
00:36:25,010 --> 00:36:27,810
The cane shall leave your back
like a tiger's pelt!

467
00:36:28,010 --> 00:36:29,430
I have no interest in sharing
the punishment.

468
00:36:29,710 --> 00:36:32,420
- You fool. What an utter fool.
- Sai! What have I done wrong?

469
00:36:32,680 --> 00:36:33,760
I could not find him anywhere.

470
00:36:33,990 --> 00:36:35,040
Nor could I!

471
00:36:35,470 --> 00:36:37,160
Are you in search of Master Klao?

472
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:42,360
Do you know Master's whereabouts?

473
00:36:54,000 --> 00:36:57,160
The House of Pleasure.

474
00:36:57,200 --> 00:36:58,360
Gasp!

475
00:37:00,510 --> 00:37:01,850
Good heavens!

476
00:37:02,800 --> 00:37:03,970
Everything has gone to ruin!

477
00:37:13,280 --> 00:37:14,280
A delightful taste.

478
00:37:15,030 --> 00:37:16,840
- Sweet and wonderful.
- You.

479
00:37:17,150 --> 00:37:18,120
You there.

480
00:37:21,360 --> 00:37:22,400
You!

481
00:37:23,240 --> 00:37:25,480
Are you talking to me?

482
00:37:30,330 --> 00:37:31,330
Aha!

483
00:37:36,140 --> 00:37:37,040
Yes.

484
00:37:37,180 --> 00:37:38,360
I am talking to you,

485
00:37:39,560 --> 00:37:40,560
Master Klao.

486
00:37:42,170 --> 00:37:43,730
Where have you been all this time?

487
00:37:44,640 --> 00:37:50,280
I was led to believe your heart
had strayed to another favored place.

488
00:37:51,560 --> 00:37:54,220
This way, this way.

489
00:37:54,250 --> 00:37:56,960
If you would, this way.

490
00:38:00,370 --> 00:38:01,070
Hey!

491
00:38:01,120 --> 00:38:03,360
Hey! Pray, help me!

492
00:38:05,560 --> 00:38:06,400
Too high.

493
00:38:07,660 --> 00:38:09,160
Oh, my.

494
00:38:13,780 --> 00:38:14,720
Master Klao.

495
00:38:15,260 --> 00:38:16,260
Today...

496
00:38:16,620 --> 00:38:19,880
We have the Seven-Headed,
Three-Clawed Dragon herbal liquor.

497
00:38:20,020 --> 00:38:22,160
It relieves body pain

498
00:38:22,270 --> 00:38:25,120
and soreness and helps you sleep well.

499
00:38:25,290 --> 00:38:27,180
Goodness. Were you to taste this,

500
00:38:27,320 --> 00:38:30,240
its potency would far surpass
even that of the Dragon...

501
00:38:30,510 --> 00:38:32,710
The Dragon... That one...

502
00:38:33,130 --> 00:38:36,600
The Dragon Horse, Seared by Fire.

503
00:38:37,210 --> 00:38:38,640
Aha.

504
00:38:43,010 --> 00:38:44,010
Here...

505
00:38:47,270 --> 00:38:48,200
Here it is.

506
00:38:50,040 --> 00:38:51,070
I'd rather not.

507
00:38:51,120 --> 00:38:53,480
I have no taste for herbal liquor.

508
00:38:55,690 --> 00:38:57,570
No taste for herbal liquor?

509
00:38:58,000 --> 00:38:59,740
Last time you had half a jar.

510
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:01,240
If you did,

511
00:39:01,540 --> 00:39:02,860
I daresay you'd take the whole pot.

512
00:39:06,160 --> 00:39:09,780
Well, I prefer...

513
00:39:10,150 --> 00:39:11,040
Soju!

514
00:39:12,120 --> 00:39:13,260
Jjan!

515
00:39:23,330 --> 00:39:24,330
"Jjan"?

516
00:39:25,940 --> 00:39:26,940
Huh?

517
00:39:27,730 --> 00:39:28,730
Like "jangle"?

518
00:39:29,830 --> 00:39:30,720
Huh?

519
00:39:31,250 --> 00:39:33,240
So the rumor that

520
00:39:33,830 --> 00:39:35,820
Master Klao has gone mad

521
00:39:36,290 --> 00:39:37,670
is true?

522
00:39:46,840 --> 00:39:48,030
Excuse me.

523
00:39:48,090 --> 00:39:49,930
What is this yellow fruit?

524
00:39:49,960 --> 00:39:50,850
Uh...

525
00:39:50,880 --> 00:39:52,870
This... No, no.

526
00:39:52,900 --> 00:39:54,000
Not that one,

527
00:39:54,030 --> 00:39:55,960
the yellow one.

528
00:39:56,340 --> 00:39:58,150
How much for the yellow fruit?

529
00:40:00,890 --> 00:40:03,370
Oh, God. How fortunate.

530
00:40:03,490 --> 00:40:05,200
Do you speak English, sir?

531
00:40:07,100 --> 00:40:08,400
- A little bit?
- Yellow?

532
00:40:09,480 --> 00:40:11,240
Come again? Yes, the yellow fruit?

533
00:40:11,430 --> 00:40:13,200
Yellow... Mango.

534
00:40:13,680 --> 00:40:15,120
Mango?

535
00:40:15,510 --> 00:40:17,400
I'll have the mango, please.

536
00:40:17,730 --> 00:40:19,460
How much for the yellow mango?

537
00:40:22,690 --> 00:40:23,560
Yellow!

538
00:40:24,490 --> 00:40:25,400
Five...

539
00:40:26,880 --> 00:40:30,200
I'll have five yellow mangoes, please.

540
00:40:32,310 --> 00:40:33,120
How much?

541
00:40:34,650 --> 00:40:36,600
Five? Okay.

542
00:40:36,890 --> 00:40:39,320
I'll give the money to you,
and you give the money to her, okay?

543
00:40:40,020 --> 00:40:42,800
I'll give it to you, you give it to her,
and I'll take the fruit.

544
00:40:45,280 --> 00:40:48,280
Well, I do bid thee a very good day,

545
00:40:48,850 --> 00:40:51,000
and thank thee

546
00:40:51,250 --> 00:40:53,120
for thy kindness, my Lord.

547
00:40:53,950 --> 00:40:55,080
Farewell.

548
00:40:55,900 --> 00:40:57,840
Yellow. Mango.

549
00:41:00,350 --> 00:41:02,360
You are truly gifted, my Lord.

550
00:41:02,550 --> 00:41:04,280
You can even speak
the tongue of the Farangi.

551
00:41:06,630 --> 00:41:08,140
I owe it all to my most esteemed mentor.

552
00:41:09,800 --> 00:41:12,200
I mean no intrusion, my Lord,

553
00:41:12,490 --> 00:41:16,000
yet I cannot help but notice
your cheerful disposition today.

554
00:41:16,120 --> 00:41:21,320
A certain someone has graced my manor with
the scent of potpourri, awaiting my return.

555
00:41:24,800 --> 00:41:25,800
Yellow.

556
00:41:25,900 --> 00:41:26,900
Mango.

557
00:41:31,240 --> 00:41:32,400
Are you intrigued?

558
00:41:33,400 --> 00:41:37,020
That was close.
So, do people here misunderstand Klao or not?

559
00:41:37,480 --> 00:41:39,410
I thought he was heartbroken about his father,

560
00:41:39,510 --> 00:41:43,160
but no, he's simply a sad baddie.

561
00:41:45,890 --> 00:41:48,360
So his visit to the brothel means...

562
00:41:49,590 --> 00:41:52,050
Do I really have to
learn the truth there myself?

563
00:41:56,520 --> 00:41:57,560
Uh, excuse me.

564
00:41:58,530 --> 00:42:02,240
Is this The House...

565
00:42:02,480 --> 00:42:04,080
Master Klao!

566
00:42:04,790 --> 00:42:06,590
Where have you been these many days?

567
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:08,760
Pim has been murmuring your name
from dawn till dusk.

568
00:42:09,670 --> 00:42:11,330
Come, let us depart, Master Klao.

569
00:42:11,360 --> 00:42:12,520
Pim?

570
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:14,250
Mother!

571
00:42:14,540 --> 00:42:16,470
Master Klao has returned!

572
00:42:16,620 --> 00:42:20,020
I'm not here to enjoy myself, by the way.

573
00:42:20,670 --> 00:42:22,970
I'm not here to have a good time, okay?

574
00:42:23,040 --> 00:42:24,990
I'm not here to have fun, okay?

575
00:42:40,470 --> 00:42:44,520
♫The flower blooms, its petals unfold,♫

576
00:42:44,610 --> 00:42:48,970
♫String upon string, in layers untold,♫

577
00:42:49,060 --> 00:42:51,420
♫Layers untold,♫

578
00:42:51,460 --> 00:42:54,850
♫By the pool of grace♫

579
00:42:55,530 --> 00:42:59,810
♫The bees caress and gently entwine,♫

580
00:43:00,000 --> 00:43:06,120
♫Their voices echo in a melody divine♫

581
00:43:07,830 --> 00:43:09,440
Your absence has been long indeed.

582
00:43:10,840 --> 00:43:14,330
A very warm welcome back to
the Pavilion of Affection, Master.

583
00:43:16,440 --> 00:43:18,760
Upon your return,

584
00:43:18,890 --> 00:43:20,720
you seem somewhat troubled, Master.

585
00:43:21,160 --> 00:43:23,550
Kindly step inside and allow the maidens
to see to your comfort

586
00:43:23,580 --> 00:43:26,050
and ease your worries.

587
00:43:26,490 --> 00:43:27,600
This way, Master.

588
00:43:28,000 --> 00:43:31,240
Long has your absence been, Master Klao.
We have missed you near unto heartbreak.

589
00:43:31,520 --> 00:43:32,720
It is so, Master.

590
00:43:32,850 --> 00:43:34,590
Pim is occupied today,

591
00:43:34,800 --> 00:43:37,570
so I shall attend to
your comfort myself, Master.

592
00:43:37,600 --> 00:43:40,360
- Or perhaps I might attend to you instead.
- Heavens, you lot!

593
00:43:40,540 --> 00:43:43,040
He has but just returned, weary and worn;
cease this dallying at once.

594
00:43:45,590 --> 00:43:46,760
Master Klao,

595
00:43:46,920 --> 00:43:49,200
pray step into the receiving room.

596
00:43:49,630 --> 00:43:51,240
- Let us make our way.
- I...

597
00:43:52,280 --> 00:43:54,760
I shall go
and fetch Pim for you presently, Master.

598
00:43:56,180 --> 00:43:57,180
Let us be on our way.

599
00:44:08,460 --> 00:44:09,850
Is it too late to turn back?

600
00:44:09,880 --> 00:44:12,690
But I won't get any clues if I do, right?

601
00:44:13,080 --> 00:44:16,840
I don't dislike you guys or anything, but...

602
00:44:18,400 --> 00:44:22,280
Phop, help me!

603
00:44:33,250 --> 00:44:35,050
Has Dear Klao finished preparing
the potpourri yet?

604
00:44:40,350 --> 00:44:41,510
My Lord,

605
00:44:43,990 --> 00:44:45,340
the fault is mine alone.

606
00:45:01,740 --> 00:45:03,160
Uh... Hi, Pim.

607
00:45:03,950 --> 00:45:06,080
Long time no see.

608
00:45:06,530 --> 00:45:07,640
I miss you.

609
00:45:08,190 --> 00:45:12,490
By the way,
when was the last time we met?

610
00:45:12,790 --> 00:45:15,120
And what did I do?

611
00:45:16,510 --> 00:45:17,680
I am

612
00:45:19,270 --> 00:45:20,440
Puang, Master.

613
00:45:45,990 --> 00:45:47,990
Truly, it has been so long

614
00:45:49,410 --> 00:45:51,180
that you have forgotten my face.

615
00:46:22,120 --> 00:46:23,120
Indeed,

616
00:46:24,140 --> 00:46:26,040
a man's tongue is woven of deceit.

617
00:47:06,840 --> 00:47:08,580
Shall we remain quiet, then?

618
00:47:10,240 --> 00:47:12,840
We might as well wait
until the candles have melted away entirely.

619
00:47:13,200 --> 00:47:14,760
For, regardless...

620
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:20,400
I remain a stranger in your memories.

621
00:47:22,600 --> 00:47:23,440
Uh...

622
00:47:27,020 --> 00:47:30,210
Well, I...

623
00:47:30,620 --> 00:47:31,920
I've lost my memory.

624
00:47:32,880 --> 00:47:33,880
Truly?

625
00:47:34,410 --> 00:47:35,280
Truly.

626
00:47:35,690 --> 00:47:36,600
Certainly?

627
00:47:36,950 --> 00:47:37,950
Certainly.

628
00:47:38,190 --> 00:47:39,190
For what reason

629
00:47:39,760 --> 00:47:42,240
do you neglect your treatment

630
00:47:42,580 --> 00:47:44,280
to come to me instead, Master Klao?

631
00:47:45,000 --> 00:47:46,120
That's a very good point.

632
00:47:46,470 --> 00:47:48,600
I'm here to see thee...

633
00:47:48,950 --> 00:47:50,240
I mean, you...

634
00:47:51,580 --> 00:47:52,580
Yeah, you...

635
00:47:52,960 --> 00:47:53,800
Why am I here again?

636
00:47:55,270 --> 00:47:56,640
Why did I come here?

637
00:48:00,040 --> 00:48:01,080
Indeed, why?

638
00:48:01,940 --> 00:48:02,940
This is

639
00:48:05,020 --> 00:48:06,760
the House of Pleasure.

640
00:48:11,490 --> 00:48:13,580
What brings

641
00:48:15,010 --> 00:48:16,420
a gentleman such as yourself

642
00:48:16,810 --> 00:48:18,840
to a place like this, Master Klao?

643
00:48:54,320 --> 00:48:56,320
No... Please, no...

644
00:49:04,480 --> 00:49:06,930
You have quite forgotten me.

645
00:49:12,470 --> 00:49:13,880
We

646
00:49:17,140 --> 00:49:20,200
have never engaged in such conduct.

647
00:49:28,150 --> 00:49:30,320
Your only intent was to sit with me

648
00:49:32,940 --> 00:49:34,180
and visit me.

649
00:49:36,080 --> 00:49:37,340
Uh, I...

650
00:49:38,610 --> 00:49:41,440
I was only here to talk to you?

651
00:49:42,180 --> 00:49:43,180
Indeed.

652
00:49:44,990 --> 00:49:46,420
You were here simply to speak with me.

653
00:49:48,850 --> 00:49:50,960
Never once have you
overstepped your bounds.

654
00:49:56,800 --> 00:49:57,790
Why?

655
00:49:59,480 --> 00:50:00,480
And...

656
00:50:01,540 --> 00:50:04,840
how did we get to know each other?

657
00:50:05,530 --> 00:50:08,360
I wasn't here to have fun?

658
00:50:11,610 --> 00:50:12,870
No, Master.

659
00:50:14,500 --> 00:50:16,200
You have simply held me in your fond regard

660
00:50:17,990 --> 00:50:19,390
because...

661
00:50:20,030 --> 00:50:22,300
upon our very first encounter,

662
00:50:23,460 --> 00:50:24,860
I was...

663
00:50:24,970 --> 00:50:27,110
Where on earth is Pim?! Huh?!

664
00:50:27,940 --> 00:50:28,940
- Uh...
- Speak!

665
00:50:28,990 --> 00:50:29,880
Well...

666
00:50:44,580 --> 00:50:45,900
So it is you, Klao.

667
00:50:46,270 --> 00:50:47,620
You have snatched her away from me.

668
00:50:48,500 --> 00:50:50,240
You were well aware I had claimed her,

669
00:50:50,340 --> 00:50:52,210
yet you dared slight me thus.

670
00:50:52,500 --> 00:50:53,500
So what of it?

671
00:50:53,820 --> 00:50:55,390
I have never allowed anyone to claim me.

672
00:50:56,290 --> 00:50:58,000
As Master Klao reached me first,

673
00:50:58,410 --> 00:51:00,090
my presence is his.

674
00:51:01,060 --> 00:51:02,980
- Let us return inside.
- You shall not go!

675
00:51:04,920 --> 00:51:07,840
Curse you, Sopha. I told you, did I not?
Pim is mine, and mine alone.

676
00:51:07,870 --> 00:51:09,800
How dare you let anyone else have her!

677
00:51:10,310 --> 00:51:11,340
You...

678
00:51:11,650 --> 00:51:13,560
You said you would go
to the outlying cities.

679
00:51:16,880 --> 00:51:18,000
Yet I have returned, have I not?

680
00:51:21,280 --> 00:51:22,450
Hand over Pim.

681
00:51:23,600 --> 00:51:24,420
Now.

682
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:25,880
No.

683
00:51:27,350 --> 00:51:28,280
Pim.

684
00:51:29,900 --> 00:51:31,440
Come to me this instant!

685
00:51:31,560 --> 00:51:32,560
Be quick!

686
00:51:34,980 --> 00:51:35,660
Damn you!

687
00:51:37,530 --> 00:51:38,980
Stay out of this!

688
00:51:46,410 --> 00:51:48,400
Do you have a death wish, Klao? Huh?!

689
00:51:48,440 --> 00:51:49,690
Cease this at once!!

690
00:51:57,620 --> 00:51:58,560
Dear Klao.

691
00:51:59,760 --> 00:52:01,070
For what purpose have you come here?

692
00:52:05,350 --> 00:52:06,240
I...

693
00:52:06,510 --> 00:52:07,400
Sopha,

694
00:52:07,900 --> 00:52:09,080
see them inside.

695
00:52:09,190 --> 00:52:10,120
Yes, my Lord.

696
00:52:10,490 --> 00:52:12,080
Make haste...

697
00:52:13,500 --> 00:52:14,320
Make haste.

698
00:52:17,690 --> 00:52:18,480
Now!

699
00:52:20,200 --> 00:52:21,080
Come.

700
00:52:35,270 --> 00:52:36,270
Cherd.

701
00:52:36,620 --> 00:52:37,620
Come with me at once.

702
00:52:40,200 --> 00:52:41,200
Dear Klao,

703
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:42,700
return to your manor,

704
00:52:43,230 --> 00:52:44,380
lest Lord Phop worry for you.

705
00:52:46,440 --> 00:52:48,270
If Klao does not leave,
then neither shall I.

706
00:52:48,310 --> 00:52:49,240
Cherd.

707
00:52:54,800 --> 00:52:56,180
Stay here if you want so damn much.

708
00:53:23,510 --> 00:53:26,660
Damn, Phop's probably already back
at the manor!

709
00:53:31,210 --> 00:53:32,920
Why should I be afraid of him
being upset with me?

710
00:53:33,280 --> 00:53:35,960
I'll hit back if he gets upset.

711
00:53:44,450 --> 00:53:48,960
But it's getting dark,
so I have no choice but to head back.

712
00:54:19,060 --> 00:54:20,560
Take shelter from the rain with me, child.

713
00:54:20,680 --> 00:54:22,420
Child, come here.

714
00:54:24,210 --> 00:54:25,390
It's okay. I'm fine.

715
00:54:28,050 --> 00:54:29,820
Come in here, or you may fall ill, child.

716
00:54:29,950 --> 00:54:31,670
- Thank you.
- Pray do not fall ill now.

717
00:54:53,940 --> 00:54:55,520
I can wait no longer.

718
00:54:57,220 --> 00:54:59,560
Kong, ready the vessel.

719
00:55:04,000 --> 00:55:05,000
Phop,

720
00:55:05,540 --> 00:55:06,990
the rain is falling.

721
00:55:07,220 --> 00:55:09,160
To set sail now would be perilous.

722
00:55:09,990 --> 00:55:11,740
He lacks experience in handling a boat.

723
00:55:11,920 --> 00:55:13,760
Would that not be a far greater risk?

724
00:55:28,910 --> 00:55:32,260
By now, Phop must be terribly worried.

725
00:55:42,350 --> 00:55:43,520
Hold on a second.

726
00:55:43,970 --> 00:55:44,970
Uncle.

727
00:55:45,630 --> 00:55:46,600
Uncle!

728
00:55:48,760 --> 00:55:49,560
Uncle!!

729
00:55:51,710 --> 00:55:53,140
Uh... Uncle.

730
00:55:54,710 --> 00:55:55,560
I mean, sir...

731
00:55:56,920 --> 00:55:59,600
I can't handle a boat very well.

732
00:56:00,550 --> 00:56:04,140
Can you escort me to my manor?

733
00:56:44,480 --> 00:56:48,170
♫Still thinking of you and only you♫

734
00:56:48,200 --> 00:56:52,810
♫The thought of your tears
is what frightens me♫

735
00:56:52,840 --> 00:57:01,000
♫Wishing rains and skies
never take your smile away♫

736
00:57:23,360 --> 00:57:25,330
Phop, I'm sorry.

737
00:57:25,360 --> 00:57:28,320
Master Klao has been out in the scorching sun,
watching over you all day, my Lord.

738
00:57:28,360 --> 00:57:31,100
By evening, he began to lapse
into delirium, as you see.

739
00:57:31,180 --> 00:57:32,360
I have made myself clear.

740
00:57:32,440 --> 00:57:33,840
I see you only as a brother.

741
00:57:33,920 --> 00:57:35,280
I could never feel otherwise.

742
00:57:35,980 --> 00:57:37,440
I ought not to have fallen for you.

743
00:57:38,660 --> 00:57:39,660
Phop!

744
00:57:40,370 --> 00:57:41,480
- What is the matter?!
- I had a nightmare.

745
00:57:41,850 --> 00:57:43,050
Tonight,

746
00:57:43,770 --> 00:57:45,320
might you share my bed?

747
00:57:47,800 --> 00:57:51,390
♫Still thinking of you and only you♫

748
00:57:51,430 --> 00:57:56,030
♫The thought of your tears
is what frightens me♫

749
00:57:56,070 --> 00:58:04,310
♫Wishing rains and skies
never take your smile away♫

750
00:58:04,340 --> 00:58:13,340
♫Every plea I make, please let it reach you♫

751
00:58:13,370 --> 00:58:17,710
♫Don't leave this heart
lost in worry and plea♫

752
00:58:17,740 --> 00:58:21,310
♫Please take care of it for me♫

753
00:58:43,000 --> 00:58:47,000
[Love Upon a Time Series]
